81 years ago, FDR signed the GI Bill, offering veterans access to life-changing benefits.

But in practice, most Black veterans were denied them—especially access to home loans programs.

@RepMoulton and I introduced the VA Housing Loan Forever Act to help right that wrong.

Far too many have suffered from heightened penalties between crack and powder cocaine.

The failed “War on Drugs” leaves a moral stain on our criminal justice system. It was ineffective, misguided, and most harmful to communities of color.

@POTUS' decision to commute nearly 2,500 people convicted of non-violent drug offenses marks a pivotal step to ensure these individuals are no longer enduring unfair punishment.

Today, I was honored to be sworn into the 119th Congress to continue serving South Carolina's 6th Congressional District.

@HouseDemocrats are committed to lowering costs and leveling the playing field for all.

The success of America is dependent upon a Congress that can put people over partisan politics, govern, and deliver real change.

The pathway to a strong, inclusive community begins by recognizing and celebrating the common bonds that unite people of diverse faiths.

